lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Microsoft Signs Publishing Deal With Designers of 'EverQ</span><hr size=1> McQuaid was never about &quot;The MUD Community&quot; and he left basically because Sony was pushing for changes that the game players had been begging for for years and he had refused to implement. He was always about making money off of a concept he knew had a built in audience. He said so in many interviews. He was never all that pro-player, in fact he was sort of notoriously anti-player and felt we didn't understand his &quot;Vision&quot;.<br><br>IMO, many of the new changes they've made since enhance my playing of the game tremendously, like channels and filters. Some suck, like the proliferation of keys.<br><br>But on the whole I'd say the game benefitted by his departure, and I shudder to think what backwards monstrosity his Vision will create this time with the backing of the evil ones.  <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39557" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Click Here to See My Stuff!" BORDER=0 SRC="http://server.counter-strike.net/images/misc/thoric.gif"></A> <BR>Click on my sig to see my gear.<br><br>"I refuse to engage in a duel of wits with an unarmed man" <br>- Francis Fay<BR><br>"July 4. Statistics show that we lose more fools on this day than in all the other days of the year put together. <br>This proves, by the number left in stock, that one fourth of July per year is now inadequate, the country has grown so." <br>- Mark Twain</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm70.showPrevMessage?topicID=216.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm70.showNextMessage?topicID=216.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm70.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=216.topic&i